  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Continuing Conquest of Canaan'
      title: The Continuing Conquest of Canaan
      number: 1
      content: "  After the death of Joshua, the people of Israel inquired of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CWho shall go up first for us against the
        Canaanites, to fight against them?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CJudah shall go up; behold,
        I have given the land into his hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Judah said to Simeon his brother, \u201CCome up with me into
        the territory allotted to me, that we may fight against the Canaanites. And
        I likewise will go with you into the territory allotted to you.\u201D So
        Simeon went with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then Judah went up and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave the Canaanites
        and the Perizzites into their hand, and they defeated 10,000 of them at Bezek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They found Adoni-bezek at Bezek and fought against him and defeated
        the Canaanites and the Perizzites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Adoni-bezek fled, but they pursued him and caught him and cut off
        his thumbs and his big toes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Adoni-bezek said, \u201CSeventy kings with their thumbs and their
        big toes cut off used to pick up scraps under my table. As I have done, so
        God has repaid me.\u201D And they brought him to Jerusalem, and he died there.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  And the men of Judah fought against Jerusalem and captured it and
        struck it with the edge of the sword and set the city on fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And afterward the men of Judah went down to fight against the Canaanites
        who lived in the hill country, in the Negeb, and in the lowland. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Judah went against the Canaanites who lived in Hebron (now the
        name of Hebron was formerly Kiriath-arba), and they defeated Sheshai and
        Ahiman and Talmai.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'From there they went against the inhabitants of Debir. The name of
        Debir was formerly Kiriath-sepher. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Caleb said, \u201CHe who attacks Kiriath-sepher and captures
        it, I will give him Achsah my daughter for a wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Othniel the son of Kenaz, Caleb\u2019s younger brother, captured
        it. And he gave him Achsah his daughter for a wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When she came to him, she urged him to ask her father for a field.
        And she dismounted from her donkey, and Caleb said to her, \u201CWhat do
        you want?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "She said to him, \u201CGive me a blessing. Since you have set me
        in the land of the Negeb, give me also springs of water.\u201D And Caleb
        gave her the upper springs and the lower springs.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the descendants of the Kenite, Moses\u2019 father-in-law, went
        up with the people of Judah from the city of palms into the wilderness of
        Judah, which lies in the Negeb near Arad, and they went and settled with
        the people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Judah went with Simeon his brother, and they defeated the Canaanites
        who inhabited Zephath and devoted it to destruction. So the name of the city
        was called Hormah.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:17 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Judah also captured Gaza with its territory, and Ashkelon with its
        territory, and Ekron with its territory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was with Judah, and he took possession
        of the hill country, but he could not drive out the inhabitants of the plain
        because they had chariots of iron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Hebron was given to Caleb, as Moses had said. And he drove out
        from it the three sons of Anak. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But the people of Benjamin did not drive out the Jebusites who lived
        in Jerusalem, so the Jebusites have lived with the people of Benjamin in
        Jerusalem to this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The house of Joseph also went up against Bethel, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        was with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And the house of Joseph scouted out Bethel. (Now the name of the
        city was formerly Luz.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the spies saw a man coming out of the city, and they said to
        him, \u201CPlease show us the way into the city, and we will deal kindly
        with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And he showed them the way into the city. And they struck the city
        with the edge of the sword, but they let the man and all his family go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Failure to Complete the Conquest'
      title: Failure to Complete the Conquest
      number: 26
      content: 'And the man went to the land of the Hittites and built a city and
        called its name Luz. That is its name to this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  Manasseh did not drive out the inhabitants of Beth-shean and its
        villages, or Taanach and its villages, or the inhabitants of Dor and its
        villages, or the inhabitants of Ibleam and its villages, or the inhabitants
        of Megiddo and its villages, for the Canaanites persisted in dwelling in
        that land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'When Israel grew strong, they put the Canaanites to forced labor,
        but did not drive them out completely.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '  And Ephraim did not drive out the Canaanites who lived in Gezer,
        so the Canaanites lived in Gezer among them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Zebulun did not drive out the inhabitants of Kitron, or the inhabitants
        of Nahalol, so the Canaanites lived among them, but became subject to forced
        labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '  Asher did not drive out the inhabitants of Acco, or the inhabitants
        of Sidon or of Ahlab or of Achzib or of Helbah or of Aphik or of Rehob, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'so the Asherites lived among the Canaanites, the inhabitants of the
        land, for they did not drive them out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Naphtali did not drive out the inhabitants of Beth-shemesh, or the
        inhabitants of Beth-anath, so they lived among the Canaanites, the inhabitants
        of the land. Nevertheless, the inhabitants of Beth-shemesh and of Beth-anath
        became subject to forced labor for them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '  The Amorites pressed the people of Dan back into the hill country,
        for they did not allow them to come down to the plain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The Amorites persisted in dwelling in Mount Heres, in Aijalon, and
        in Shaalbim, but the hand of the house of Joseph rested heavily on them,
        and they became subject to forced labor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: And the border of the Amorites ran from the ascent of Akrabbim, from
        Sela and upward.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Disobedience"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Disobedience"
      number: 1
      content: "  Now the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> went up from Gilgal
        to Bochim. And he said, \u201CI brought you up from Egypt and brought you
        into the land that I swore to give to your fathers. I said, \u2018I will
        never break my covenant with you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and you shall make no covenant with the inhabitants of this land;
        you shall break down their altars.\u2019 But you have not obeyed my voice.
        What is this you have done? "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So now I say, I will not drive them out before you, but they shall
        become thorns in your sides, and their gods shall be a snare to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'As soon as the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke these
        words to all the people of Israel, the people lifted up their voices and
        wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: The Death of Joshua'
      title: The Death of Joshua
      number: 5
      content: 'And they called the name of that place Bochim.[[COMMENT(0)]] And
        they sacrificed there to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:5 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When Joshua dismissed the people, the people of Israel went each
        to his inheritance to take possession of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the people served the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> all the days
        of Joshua, and all the days of the elders who outlived Joshua, who had seen
        all the great work that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had done for Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Joshua the son of Nun, the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        died at the age of 110 years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And they buried him within the boundaries of his inheritance in Timnath-heres,
        in the hill country of Ephraim, north of the mountain of Gaash. '
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Israel\u2019s Unfaithfulness"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Unfaithfulness"
      number: 10
      content: 'And all that generation also were gathered to their fathers. And
        there arose another generation after them who did not know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        or the work that he had done for Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  And the people of Israel did what was evil in the sight of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and served the Baals. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they abandoned the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of their
        fathers, who had brought them out of the land of Egypt. They went after other
        gods, from among the gods of the peoples who were around them, and bowed
        down to them. And they provoked the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'They abandoned the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  and served the Baals
        and the Ashtaroth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was kindled against
        Israel, and he gave them over to plunderers, who plundered them. And he sold
        them into the hand of their surrounding enemies, so that they could no longer
        withstand their enemies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The  Raises Up Judges'
      title: The  Raises Up Judges
      number: 15
      content: 'Whenever they marched out, the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        was against them for harm, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had warned,
        and as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had sworn to them. And they were in
        terrible distress.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> raised up judges, who saved
        them out of the hand of those who plundered them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Yet they did not listen to their judges, for they whored after other
        gods and bowed down to them. They soon turned aside from the way in which
        their fathers had walked, who had obeyed the commandments of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and they did not do so. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Whenever the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> raised up judges for them,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was with the judge, and he saved them from
        the hand of their enemies all the days of the judge. For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        was moved to pity by their groaning because of those who afflicted and oppressed
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But whenever the judge died, they turned back and were more corrupt
        than their fathers, going after other gods, serving them and bowing down
        to them. They did not drop any of their practices or their stubborn ways. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was kindled against
        Israel, and he said, \u201CBecause this people have transgressed my covenant
        that I commanded their fathers and have not obeyed my voice, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'I will no longer drive out before them any of the nations that Joshua
        left when he died, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "in order to test Israel by them, whether they will take care to walk
        in the way of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> as their fathers did, or not.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> left those nations, not driving
        them out quickly, and he did not give them into the hand of Joshua.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '    Now these are the nations that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        left, to test Israel by them, that is, all in Israel who had not experienced
        all the wars in Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'It was only in order that the generations of the people of Israel
        might know war, to teach war to those who had not known it before. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'These are the nations: the five lords of the Philistines and all
        the Canaanites and the Sidonians and the Hivites who lived on Mount Lebanon,
        from Mount Baal-hermon as far as Lebo-hamath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They were for the testing of Israel, to know whether Israel would
        obey the commandments of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, which he commanded
        their fathers by the hand of Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So the people of Israel lived among the Canaanites, the Hittites,
        the Amorites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Othniel'
      title: Othniel
      number: 6
      content: 'And their daughters they took to themselves for wives, and their
        own daughters they gave to their sons, and they served their gods.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  And the people of Israel did what was evil in the sight of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. They forgot the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        their God and served the Baals and the Asheroth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Therefore the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was kindled
        against Israel, and he sold them into the hand of Cushan-rishathaim king
        of Mesopotamia. And the people of Israel served Cushan-rishathaim eight years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But when the people of Israel cried out to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> raised up a deliverer for the people of Israel,
        who saved them, Othniel the son of Kenaz, Caleb\u2019s younger brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was upon him, and he
        judged Israel. He went out to war, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave
        Cushan-rishathaim king of Mesopotamia into his hand. And his hand prevailed
        over Cushan-rishathaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Ehud'
      title: Ehud
      number: 11
      content: 'So the land had rest forty years. Then Othniel the son of Kenaz died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  And the people of Israel again did what was evil in the sight of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> strengthened
        Eglon the king of Moab against Israel, because they had done what was evil
        in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He gathered to himself the Ammonites and the Amalekites, and went
        and defeated Israel. And they took possession of the city of palms. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the people of Israel served Eglon the king of Moab eighteen years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the people of Israel cried out to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> raised up for them a deliverer, Ehud,
        the son of Gera, the Benjaminite, a left-handed man. The people of Israel
        sent tribute by him to Eglon the king of Moab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Ehud made for himself a sword with two edges, a cubit[[COMMENT(0)]]
        in length, and he bound it on his right thigh under his clothes. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:16 '
        content: A was about 18 inches or 45 centimeters
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And he presented the tribute to Eglon king of Moab. Now Eglon was
        a very fat man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And when Ehud had finished presenting the tribute, he sent away the
        people who carried the tribute. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But he himself turned back at the idols near Gilgal and said, \u201CI
        have a secret message for you, O king.\u201D And he commanded, \u201CSilence.\u201D
        And all his attendants went out from his presence. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Ehud came to him as he was sitting alone in his cool roof chamber.
        And Ehud said, \u201CI have a message from God for you.\u201D And he arose
        from his seat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Ehud reached with his left hand, took the sword from his right
        thigh, and thrust it into his belly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the hilt also went in after the blade, and the fat closed over
        the blade, for he did not pull the sword out of his belly; and the dung came
        out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then Ehud went out into the porch[[COMMENT(0)]] and closed the doors
        of the roof chamber behind him and locked them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:23 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "When he had gone, the servants came, and when they saw that the doors
        of the roof chamber were locked, they thought, \u201CSurely he is relieving
        himself in the closet of the cool chamber.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And they waited till they were embarrassed. But when he still did
        not open the doors of the roof chamber, they took the key and opened them,
        and there lay their lord dead on the floor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Ehud escaped while they delayed, and he passed beyond the idols and
        escaped to Seirah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When he arrived, he sounded the trumpet in the hill country of Ephraim.
        Then the people of Israel went down with him from the hill country, and he
        was their leader. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CFollow after me, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has given your enemies the Moabites into your hand.\u201D So they went down
        after him and seized the fords of the Jordan against the Moabites and did
        not allow anyone to pass over. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And they killed at that time about 10,000 of the Moabites, all strong,
        able-bodied men; not a man escaped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: Shamgar'
      title: Shamgar
      number: 30
      content: 'So Moab was subdued that day under the hand of Israel. And the land
        had rest for eighty years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: After him was Shamgar the son of Anath, who killed 600 of the Philistines
        with an oxgoad, and he also saved Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Deborah and Barak'
      title: Deborah and Barak
      number: 1
      content: '    And the people of Israel again did what was evil in the sight
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> after Ehud died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  sold them into the hand of Jabin
        king of Canaan, who reigned in Hazor. The commander of his army was Sisera,
        who lived in Harosheth-hagoyim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then the people of Israel cried out to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        for help, for he had 900 chariots of iron and he oppressed the people of
        Israel cruelly for twenty years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now Deborah, a prophetess, the wife of Lappidoth, was judging Israel
        at that time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'She used to sit under the palm of Deborah between Ramah and Bethel
        in the hill country of Ephraim, and the people of Israel came up to her for
        judgment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "She sent and summoned Barak the son of Abinoam from Kedesh-naphtali
        and said to him, \u201CHas not the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of
        Israel, commanded you, \u2018Go, gather your men at Mount Tabor, taking 10,000
        from the people of Naphtali and the people of Zebulun. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And I will draw out Sisera, the general of Jabin\u2019s army, to
        meet you by the river Kishon with his chariots and his troops, and I will
        give him into your hand\u2019?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Barak said to her, \u201CIf you will go with me, I will go, but if
        you will not go with me, I will not go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And she said, \u201CI will surely go with you. Nevertheless, the
        road on which you are going will not lead to your glory, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will sell Sisera into the hand of a woman.\u201D Then Deborah arose and went
        with Barak to Kedesh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Barak called out Zebulun and Naphtali to Kedesh. And 10,000 men
        went up at his heels, and Deborah went up with him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now Heber the Kenite had separated from the Kenites, the descendants
        of Hobab the father-in-law of Moses, and had pitched his tent as far away
        as the oak in Zaanannim, which is near Kedesh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When Sisera was told that Barak the son of Abinoam had gone up to
        Mount Tabor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Sisera called out all his chariots, 900 chariots of iron, and all
        the men who were with him, from Harosheth-hagoyim to the river Kishon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Deborah said to Barak, \u201CUp! For this is the day in which
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has given Sisera into your hand. Does not
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> go out before you?\u201D So Barak went down
        from Mount Tabor with 10,000 men following him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> routed Sisera and all his chariots
        and all his army before Barak by the edge of the sword. And Sisera got down
        from his chariot and fled away on foot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Barak pursued the chariots and the army to Harosheth-hagoyim,
        and all the army of Sisera fell by the edge of the sword; not a man was left.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But Sisera fled away on foot to the tent of Jael, the wife of Heber
        the Kenite, for there was peace between Jabin the king of Hazor and the house
        of Heber the Kenite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Jael came out to meet Sisera and said to him, \u201CTurn aside,
        my lord; turn aside to me; do not be afraid.\u201D So he turned aside to
        her into the tent, and she covered him with a rug. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he said to her, \u201CPlease give me a little water to drink,
        for I am thirsty.\u201D So she opened a skin of milk and gave him a drink
        and covered him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And he said to her, \u201CStand at the opening of the tent, and if
        any man comes and asks you, \u2018Is anyone here?\u2019 say, \u2018No.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But Jael the wife of Heber took a tent peg, and took a hammer in
        her hand. Then she went softly to him and drove the peg into his temple until
        it went down into the ground while he was lying fast asleep from weariness.
        So he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And behold, as Barak was pursuing Sisera, Jael went out to meet him
        and said to him, \u201CCome, and I will show you the man whom you are seeking.\u201D
        So he went in to her tent, and there lay Sisera dead, with the tent peg in
        his temple.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  So on that day God subdued Jabin the king of Canaan before the
        people of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: And the hand of the people of Israel pressed harder and harder against
        Jabin the king of Canaan, until they destroyed Jabin king of Canaan.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Song of Deborah and Barak'
      title: The Song of Deborah and Barak
      number: 1
      content: '    Then sang Deborah and Barak the son of Abinoam on that day:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThat the leaders took the lead in Israel,that the people offered
        themselves willingly,bless the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CHear, O kings; give ear, O princes;to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        I will sing;I will make melody to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God
        of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201C<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, when you went out from Seir,when
        you marched from the region of Edom,  the earth trembledand the heavens dropped,yes,
        the clouds dropped water.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The mountains quaked before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  even
        Sinai before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,[[COMMENT(0)]] the God of Israel.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:5 '
        content: 'Or <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span><span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>  '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIn the days of Shamgar, son of Anath,in the days of Jael, the
        highways were abandoned,and travelers kept to the byways.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The villagers ceased in Israel;they ceased to be until I arose;I,
        Deborah, arose as a mother in Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  When new gods were chosen,then war was in the gates.  Was shield
        or spear to be seenamong forty thousand in Israel?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'My heart goes out to the commanders of Israelwho offered themselves
        willingly among the people.Bless the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CTell of it, you who ride on white donkeys,you who sit on rich
        carpets[[COMMENT(0)]]and you who walk by the way.  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:10 '
        content: 'The meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain; it may connote '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "To the sound of musicians[[COMMENT(0)]] at the watering places,there
        they repeat the righteous triumphs of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,the
        righteous triumphs of his villagers in Israel.\u201CThen down to the gates
        marched the people of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:11 '
        content: Or ; the meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  \u201CAwake, awake, Deborah!Awake, awake, break out in a song!Arise,
        Barak, lead away your captives,O son of Abinoam.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then down marched the remnant of the noble;the people of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        marched down for me against the mighty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "From Ephraim their root they marched down into the valley,[[COMMENT(0)]]following
        you, Benjamin, with your kinsmen;from Machir marched down the commanders,and
        from Zebulun those who bear the lieutenant\u2019s staff;  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:14 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew Hebrew '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the princes of Issachar came with Deborah,and Issachar faithful to
        Barak;into the valley they rushed at his heels.Among the clans of Reubenthere
        were great searchings of heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Why did you sit still among the sheepfolds,to hear the whistling
        for the flocks?Among the clans of Reubenthere were great searchings of heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Gilead stayed beyond the Jordan;  and Dan, why did he stay with
        the ships?  Asher sat still at the coast of the sea,staying by his landings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Zebulun is a people who risked their lives to the death;  Naphtali,
        too, on the heights of the field.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThe kings came, they fought;then fought the kings of Canaan,at
        Taanach, by the waters of Megiddo;  they got no spoils of silver.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  From heaven the stars fought,from their courses they fought against
        Sisera.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  The torrent Kishon swept them away,the ancient torrent, the torrent
        Kishon.March on, my soul, with might!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CThen loud beat the horses\u2019 hoofswith the galloping, galloping
        of his steeds.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CCurse Meroz, says the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,curse
        its inhabitants thoroughly,  because they did not come to the help of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,to the help of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        against the mighty.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CMost blessed of women be Jael,the wife of Heber the Kenite,of
        tent-dwelling women most blessed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "  He asked for water and she gave him milk;she brought him curds
        in a noble\u2019s bowl.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  She sent her hand to the tent pegand her right hand to the workmen\u2019s
        mallet;she struck Sisera;she crushed his head;she shattered and pierced his
        temple.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Between her feethe sank, he fell, he lay still;between her feethe
        sank, he fell;where he sank,there he fell\u2014dead.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  \u201COut of the window she peered,the mother of Sisera wailed
        through the lattice:\u2018Why is his chariot so long in coming?Why tarry
        the hoofbeats of his chariots?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Her wisest princesses answer,indeed, she answers herself,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u2018Have they not found and divided the spoil?\u2014A womb or two
        for every man;spoil of dyed materials for Sisera,spoil of dyed materials
        embroidered,two pieces of dyed work embroidered for the neck as spoil?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "  \u201CSo may all your enemies perish, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!But
        your friends be like the sun as he rises in his might.\u201D  And the land
        had rest for forty years."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Midian Oppresses Israel'
      title: Midian Oppresses Israel
      number: 1
      content: '    The people of Israel did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave them into the hand of Midian seven
        years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the hand of Midian overpowered Israel, and because of Midian
        the people of Israel made for themselves the dens that are in the mountains
        and the caves and the strongholds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For whenever the Israelites planted crops, the Midianites and the
        Amalekites and the people of the East would come up against them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They would encamp against them and devour the produce of the land,
        as far as Gaza, and leave no sustenance in Israel and no sheep or ox or donkey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For they would come up with their livestock and their tents; they
        would come like locusts in number\u2014both they and their camels could not
        be counted\u2014so that they laid waste the land as they came in. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Israel was brought very low because of Midian. And the people
        of Israel cried out for help to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When the people of Israel cried out to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        on account of the Midianites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent a prophet to the people of Israel.
        And he said to them, \u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the
        God of Israel: I led you up from Egypt and brought you out of the house of
        slavery. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And I delivered you from the hand of the Egyptians and from the hand
        of all who oppressed you, and drove them out before you and gave you their
        land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Call of Gideon'
      title: The Call of Gideon
      number: 10
      content: "And I said to you, \u2018I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God; you shall not fear the gods of the Amorites in whose land you dwell.\u2019
        But you have not obeyed my voice.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came and sat under
        the terebinth at Ophrah, which belonged to Joash the Abiezrite, while his
        son Gideon was beating out wheat in the winepress to hide it from the Midianites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> appeared to him
        and said to him, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is with you, O mighty
        man of valor.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Gideon said to him, \u201CPlease, my lord, if the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is with us, why then has all this happened to us? And where are all his wonderful
        deeds that our fathers recounted to us, saying, \u2018Did not the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        bring us up from Egypt?\u2019 But now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has
        forsaken us and given us into the hand of Midian.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>[[COMMENT(0)]] turned to him and
        said, \u201CGo in this might of yours and save Israel from the hand of Midian;
        do not I send you?\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '6:14 '
        content: Septuagint <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>;
          also verse 16
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CPlease, Lord, how can I save Israel? Behold,
        my clan is the weakest in Manasseh, and I am the least in my father\u2019s
        house.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to him, \u201CBut I will
        be with you, and you shall strike the Midianites as one man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CIf now I have found favor in your eyes,
        then show me a sign that it is you who speak with me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Please do not depart from here until I come to you and bring out
        my present and set it before you.\u201D And he said, \u201CI will stay till
        you return.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Gideon went into his house and prepared a young goat and unleavened
        cakes from an ephah[[COMMENT(0)]] of flour. The meat he put in a basket,
        and the broth he put in a pot, and brought them to him under the terebinth
        and presented them. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:19 '
        content: An was about 3/5 bushel or 22 liters
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And the angel of God said to him, \u201CTake the meat and the unleavened
        cakes, and put them on this rock, and pour the broth over them.\u201D And
        he did so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> reached out the
        tip of the staff that was in his hand and touched the meat and the unleavened
        cakes. And fire sprang up from the rock and consumed the meat and the unleavened
        cakes. And the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> vanished from his
        sight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Gideon perceived that he was the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        And Gideon said, \u201CAlas, O Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>! For now I
        have seen the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> face to face.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to him, \u201CPeace be to
        you. Do not fear; you shall not die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then Gideon built an altar there to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and called it, The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> Is Peace. To this day it still
        stands at Ophrah, which belongs to the Abiezrites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "That night the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to him, \u201CTake
        your father\u2019s bull, and the second bull seven years old, and pull down
        the altar of Baal that your father has, and cut down the Asherah that is
        beside it "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "and build an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God on
        the top of the stronghold here, with stones laid in due order. Then take
        the second bull and offer it as a burnt offering with the wood of the Asherah
        that you shall cut down.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Gideon Destroys the Altar of Baal'
      title: Gideon Destroys the Altar of Baal
      number: 27
      content: 'So Gideon took ten men of his servants and did as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had told him. But because he was too afraid of his family and the men of
        the town to do it by day, he did it by night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'When the men of the town rose early in the morning, behold, the altar
        of Baal was broken down, and the Asherah beside it was cut down, and the
        second bull was offered on the altar that had been built. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And they said to one another, \u201CWho has done this thing?\u201D
        And after they had searched and inquired, they said, \u201CGideon the son
        of Joash has done this thing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then the men of the town said to Joash, \u201CBring out your son,
        that he may die, for he has broken down the altar of Baal and cut down the
        Asherah beside it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But Joash said to all who stood against him, \u201CWill you contend
        for Baal? Or will you save him? Whoever contends for him shall be put to
        death by morning. If he is a god, let him contend for himself, because his
        altar has been broken down.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Therefore on that day Gideon[[COMMENT(0)]] was called Jerubbaal,
        that is to say, \u201CLet Baal contend against him,\u201D because he broke
        down his altar.  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:32 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Now all the Midianites and the Amalekites and the people of the East
        came together, and they crossed the Jordan and encamped in the Valley of
        Jezreel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'But the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> clothed Gideon,
        and he sounded the trumpet, and the Abiezrites were called out to follow
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: The Sign of the Fleece'
      title: The Sign of the Fleece
      number: 35
      content: 'And he sent messengers throughout all Manasseh, and they too were
        called out to follow him. And he sent messengers to Asher, Zebulun, and Naphtali,
        and they went up to meet them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "  Then Gideon said to God, \u201CIf you will save Israel by my hand,
        as you have said, "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "behold, I am laying a fleece of wool on the threshing floor. If there
        is dew on the fleece alone, and it is dry on all the ground, then I shall
        know that you will save Israel by my hand, as you have said.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And it was so. When he rose early next morning and squeezed the fleece,
        he wrung enough dew from the fleece to fill a bowl with water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Then Gideon said to God, \u201CLet not your anger burn against me;
        let me speak just once more. Please let me test just once more with the fleece.
        Please let it be dry on the fleece only, and on all the ground let there
        be dew.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: And God did so that night; and it was dry on the fleece only, and
        on all the ground there was dew.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Gideon\u2019s Three Hundred Men"
      title: "Gideon\u2019s Three Hundred Men"
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Jerubbaal (that is, Gideon) and all the people who were with
        him rose early and encamped beside the spring of Harod. And the camp of Midian
        was north of them, by the hill of Moreh, in the valley.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Gideon, \u201CThe people
        with you are too many for me to give the Midianites into their hand, lest
        Israel boast over me, saying, \u2018My own hand has saved me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now therefore proclaim in the ears of the people, saying, \u2018Whoever
        is fearful and trembling, let him return home and hurry away from Mount Gilead.\u2019\u201D
        Then 22,000 of the people returned, and 10,000 remained.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Gideon, \u201CThe people
        are still too many. Take them down to the water, and I will test them for
        you there, and anyone of whom I say to you, \u2018This one shall go with
        you,\u2019 shall go with you, and anyone of whom I say to you, \u2018This
        one shall not go with you,\u2019 shall not go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So he brought the people down to the water. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said to Gideon, \u201CEvery one who laps the water with his tongue, as a
        dog laps, you shall set by himself. Likewise, every one who kneels down to
        drink.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the number of those who lapped, putting their hands to their
        mouths, was 300 men, but all the rest of the people knelt down to drink water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Gideon, \u201CWith the
        300 men who lapped I will save you and give the Midianites into your hand,
        and let all the others go every man to his home.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the people took provisions in their hands, and their trumpets.
        And he sent all the rest of Israel every man to his tent, but retained the
        300 men. And the camp of Midian was below him in the valley.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "That same night the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to him, \u201CArise,
        go down against the camp, for I have given it into your hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But if you are afraid to go down, go down to the camp with Purah
        your servant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And you shall hear what they say, and afterward your hands shall
        be strengthened to go down against the camp.\u201D Then he went down with
        Purah his servant to the outposts of the armed men who were in the camp. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the Midianites and the Amalekites and all the people of the East
        lay along the valley like locusts in abundance, and their camels were without
        number, as the sand that is on the seashore in abundance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When Gideon came, behold, a man was telling a dream to his comrade.
        And he said, \u201CBehold, I dreamed a dream, and behold, a cake of barley
        bread tumbled into the camp of Midian and came to the tent and struck it
        so that it fell and turned it upside down, so that the tent lay flat.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And his comrade answered, \u201CThis is no other than the sword of
        Gideon the son of Joash, a man of Israel; God has given into his hand Midian
        and all the camp.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "As soon as Gideon heard the telling of the dream and its interpretation,
        he worshiped. And he returned to the camp of Israel and said, \u201CArise,
        for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has given the host of Midian into your
        hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And he divided the 300 men into three companies and put trumpets
        into the hands of all of them and empty jars, with torches inside the jars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CLook at me, and do likewise. When I come
        to the outskirts of the camp, do as I do. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Gideon Defeats Midian'
      title: Gideon Defeats Midian
      number: 18
      content: "When I blow the trumpet, I and all who are with me, then blow the
        trumpets also on every side of all the camp and shout, \u2018For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and for Gideon.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Gideon and the hundred men who were with him came to the outskirts
        of the camp at the beginning of the middle watch, when they had just set
        the watch. And they blew the trumpets and smashed the jars that were in their
        hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then the three companies blew the trumpets and broke the jars. They
        held in their left hands the torches, and in their right hands the trumpets
        to blow. And they cried out, \u201CA sword for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and for Gideon!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Every man stood in his place around the camp, and all the army ran.
        They cried out and fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "When they blew the 300 trumpets, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        set every man\u2019s sword against his comrade and against all the army.
        And the army fled as far as Beth-shittah toward Zererah,[[COMMENT(0)]] as
        far as the border of Abel-meholah, by Tabbath. "
      comments:
      - number: '7:22 '
        content: 'Some Hebrew manuscripts '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And the men of Israel were called out from Naphtali and from Asher
        and from all Manasseh, and they pursued after Midian.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  Gideon sent messengers throughout all the hill country of Ephraim,
        saying, \u201CCome down against the Midianites and capture the waters against
        them, as far as Beth-barah, and also the Jordan.\u201D So all the men of
        Ephraim were called out, and they captured the waters as far as Beth-barah,
        and also the Jordan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And they captured the two princes of Midian, Oreb and Zeeb. They killed
        Oreb at the rock of Oreb, and Zeeb they killed at the winepress of Zeeb.
        Then they pursued Midian, and they brought the heads of Oreb and Zeeb to
        Gideon across the Jordan.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Gideon Defeats Zebah and Zalmunna'
      title: Gideon Defeats Zebah and Zalmunna
      number: 1
      content: "    Then the men of Ephraim said to him, \u201CWhat is this that
        you have done to us, not to call us when you went to fight against Midian?\u201D
        And they accused him fiercely. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CWhat have I done now in comparison with
        you? Is not the gleaning of the grapes of Ephraim better than the grape harvest
        of Abiezer? "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "God has given into your hands the princes of Midian, Oreb and Zeeb.
        What have I been able to do in comparison with you?\u201D Then their anger[[COMMENT(0)]]
        against him subsided when he said this.  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:3 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Gideon came to the Jordan and crossed over, he and the 300 men
        who were with him, exhausted yet pursuing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So he said to the men of Succoth, \u201CPlease give loaves of bread
        to the people who follow me, for they are exhausted, and I am pursuing after
        Zebah and Zalmunna, the kings of Midian.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the officials of Succoth said, \u201CAre the hands of Zebah and
        Zalmunna already in your hand, that we should give bread to your army?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Gideon said, \u201CWell then, when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has given Zebah and Zalmunna into my hand, I will flail your flesh with the
        thorns of the wilderness and with briers.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And from there he went up to Penuel, and spoke to them in the same
        way, and the men of Penuel answered him as the men of Succoth had answered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And he said to the men of Penuel, \u201CWhen I come again in peace,
        I will break down this tower.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now Zebah and Zalmunna were in Karkor with their army, about 15,000
        men, all who were left of all the army of the people of the East, for there
        had fallen 120,000 men who drew the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Gideon went up by the way of the tent dwellers east of Nobah
        and Jogbehah and attacked the army, for the army felt secure. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Zebah and Zalmunna fled, and he pursued them and captured the
        two kings of Midian, Zebah and Zalmunna, and he threw all the army into a
        panic.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Gideon the son of Joash returned from the battle by the ascent
        of Heres. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he captured a young man of Succoth and questioned him. And he
        wrote down for him the officials and elders of Succoth, seventy-seven men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And he came to the men of Succoth and said, \u201CBehold Zebah and
        Zalmunna, about whom you taunted me, saying, \u2018Are the hands of Zebah
        and Zalmunna already in your hand, that we should give bread to your men
        who are exhausted?\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And he took the elders of the city, and he took thorns of the wilderness
        and briers and with them taught the men of Succoth a lesson. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And he broke down the tower of Penuel and killed the men of the city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then he said to Zebah and Zalmunna, \u201CWhere are the men whom
        you killed at Tabor?\u201D They answered, \u201CAs you are, so were they.
        Every one of them resembled the son of a king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he said, \u201CThey were my brothers, the sons of my mother.
        As the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives, if you had saved them alive, I
        would not kill you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So he said to Jether his firstborn, \u201CRise and kill them!\u201D
        But the young man did not draw his sword, for he was afraid, because he was
        still a young man. "
      comments: []
    - name: "21: Gideon\u2019s Ephod"
      title: "Gideon\u2019s Ephod"
      number: 21
      content: "Then Zebah and Zalmunna said, \u201CRise yourself and fall upon us,
        for as the man is, so is his strength.\u201D And Gideon arose and killed
        Zebah and Zalmunna, and he took the crescent ornaments that were on the necks
        of their camels.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the men of Israel said to Gideon, \u201CRule over us, you and
        your son and your grandson also, for you have saved us from the hand of Midian.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Gideon said to them, \u201CI will not rule over you, and my son will
        not rule over you; the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will rule over you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Gideon said to them, \u201CLet me make a request of you: every
        one of you give me the earrings from his spoil.\u201D (For they had golden
        earrings, because they were Ishmaelites.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And they answered, \u201CWe will willingly give them.\u201D And they
        spread a cloak, and every man threw in it the earrings of his spoil. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And the weight of the golden earrings that he requested was 1,700
        shekels[[COMMENT(0)]] of gold, besides the crescent ornaments and the pendants
        and the purple garments worn by the kings of Midian, and besides the collars
        that were around the necks of their camels. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:26 '
        content: A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And Gideon made an ephod of it and put it in his city, in Ophrah.
        And all Israel whored after it there, and it became a snare to Gideon and
        to his family. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: The Death of Gideon'
      title: The Death of Gideon
      number: 28
      content: 'So Midian was subdued before the people of Israel, and they raised
        their heads no more. And the land had rest forty years in the days of Gideon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '  Jerubbaal the son of Joash went and lived in his own house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now Gideon had seventy sons, his own offspring,[[COMMENT(0)]] for
        he had many wives. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:30 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And his concubine who was in Shechem also bore him a son, and he
        called his name Abimelech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And Gideon the son of Joash died in a good old age and was buried
        in the tomb of Joash his father, at Ophrah of the Abiezrites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '  As soon as Gideon died, the people of Israel turned again and whored
        after the Baals and made Baal-berith their god. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And the people of Israel did not remember the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        their God, who had delivered them from the hand of all their enemies on every
        side, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: and they did not show steadfast love to the family of Jerubbaal (that
        is, Gideon) in return for all the good that he had done to Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Abimelech\u2019s Conspiracy"
      title: "Abimelech\u2019s Conspiracy"
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Abimelech the son of Jerubbaal went to Shechem to his mother\u2019s
        relatives and said to them and to the whole clan of his mother\u2019s family, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSay in the ears of all the leaders of Shechem, \u2018Which
        is better for you, that all seventy of the sons of Jerubbaal rule over you,
        or that one rule over you?\u2019 Remember also that I am your bone and your
        flesh.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And his mother\u2019s relatives spoke all these words on his behalf
        in the ears of all the leaders of Shechem, and their hearts inclined to follow
        Abimelech, for they said, \u201CHe is our brother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they gave him seventy pieces of silver out of the house of Baal-berith
        with which Abimelech hired worthless and reckless fellows, who followed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And he went to his father\u2019s house at Ophrah and killed his brothers
        the sons of Jerubbaal, seventy men, on one stone. But Jotham the youngest
        son of Jerubbaal was left, for he hid himself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And all the leaders of Shechem came together, and all Beth-millo,
        and they went and made Abimelech king, by the oak of the pillar at Shechem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When it was told to Jotham, he went and stood on top of Mount Gerizim
        and cried aloud and said to them, \u201CListen to me, you leaders of Shechem,
        that God may listen to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The trees once went out to anoint a king over them, and they said
        to the olive tree, \u2018Reign over us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But the olive tree said to them, \u2018Shall I leave my abundance,
        by which gods and men are honored, and go hold sway over the trees?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the trees said to the fig tree, \u2018You come and reign over
        us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But the fig tree said to them, \u2018Shall I leave my sweetness and
        my good fruit and go hold sway over the trees?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the trees said to the vine, \u2018You come and reign over us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But the vine said to them, \u2018Shall I leave my wine that cheers
        God and men and go hold sway over the trees?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then all the trees said to the bramble, \u2018You come and reign
        over us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And the bramble said to the trees, \u2018If in good faith you are
        anointing me king over you, then come and take refuge in my shade, but if
        not, let fire come out of the bramble and devour the cedars of Lebanon.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CNow therefore, if you acted in good faith and integrity when
        you made Abimelech king, and if you have dealt well with Jerubbaal and his
        house and have done to him as his deeds deserved\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'for my father fought for you and risked his life and delivered you
        from the hand of Midian, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and you have risen up against my father\u2019s house this day and
        have killed his sons, seventy men on one stone, and have made Abimelech,
        the son of his female servant, king over the leaders of Shechem, because
        he is your relative\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'if you then have acted in good faith and integrity with Jerubbaal
        and with his house this day, then rejoice in Abimelech, and let him also
        rejoice in you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But if not, let fire come out from Abimelech and devour the leaders
        of Shechem and Beth-millo; and let fire come out from the leaders of Shechem
        and from Beth-millo and devour Abimelech.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: The Downfall of Abimelech'
      title: The Downfall of Abimelech
      number: 21
      content: 'And Jotham ran away and fled and went to Beer and lived there, because
        of Abimelech his brother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Abimelech ruled over Israel three years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And God sent an evil spirit between Abimelech and the leaders of
        Shechem, and the leaders of Shechem dealt treacherously with Abimelech, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'that the violence done to the seventy sons of Jerubbaal might come,
        and their blood be laid on Abimelech their brother, who killed them, and
        on the men of Shechem, who strengthened his hands to kill his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And the leaders of Shechem put men in ambush against him on the mountaintops,
        and they robbed all who passed by them along that way. And it was told to
        Abimelech.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And Gaal the son of Ebed moved into Shechem with his relatives, and
        the leaders of Shechem put confidence in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And they went out into the field and gathered the grapes from their
        vineyards and trod them and held a festival; and they went into the house
        of their god and ate and drank and reviled Abimelech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And Gaal the son of Ebed said, \u201CWho is Abimelech, and who are
        we of Shechem, that we should serve him? Is he not the son of Jerubbaal,
        and is not Zebul his officer? Serve the men of Hamor the father of Shechem;
        but why should we serve him? "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Would that this people were under my hand! Then I would remove Abimelech.
        I would say[[COMMENT(0)]] to Abimelech, \u2018Increase your army, and come
        out.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:29 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'When Zebul the ruler of the city heard the words of Gaal the son
        of Ebed, his anger was kindled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And he sent messengers to Abimelech secretly,[[COMMENT(0)]] saying,
        \u201CBehold, Gaal the son of Ebed and his relatives have come to Shechem,
        and they are stirring up the city against you. "
      comments:
      - number: '9:31 '
        content: 'Or Hebrew , or '
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now therefore, go by night, you and the people who are with you,
        and set an ambush in the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then in the morning, as soon as the sun is up, rise early and rush
        upon the city. And when he and the people who are with him come out against
        you, you may do to them as your hand finds to do.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'So Abimelech and all the men who were with him rose up by night and
        set an ambush against Shechem in four companies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And Gaal the son of Ebed went out and stood in the entrance of the
        gate of the city, and Abimelech and the people who were with him rose from
        the ambush. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And when Gaal saw the people, he said to Zebul, \u201CLook, people
        are coming down from the mountaintops!\u201D And Zebul said to him, \u201CYou
        mistake[[COMMENT(0)]] the shadow of the mountains for men.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '9:36 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Gaal spoke again and said, \u201CLook, people are coming down from
        the center of the land, and one company is coming from the direction of the
        Diviners\u2019 Oak.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Then Zebul said to him, \u201CWhere is your mouth now, you who said,
        \u2018Who is Abimelech, that we should serve him?\u2019 Are not these the
        people whom you despised? Go out now and fight with them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And Gaal went out at the head of the leaders of Shechem and fought
        with Abimelech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And Abimelech chased him, and he fled before him. And many fell wounded,
        up to the entrance of the gate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And Abimelech lived at Arumah, and Zebul drove out Gaal and his relatives,
        so that they could not dwell at Shechem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'On the following day, the people went out into the field, and Abimelech
        was told. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'He took his people and divided them into three companies and set
        an ambush in the fields. And he looked and saw the people coming out of the
        city. So he rose against them and killed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Abimelech and the company that was with him rushed forward and stood
        at the entrance of the gate of the city, while the two companies rushed upon
        all who were in the field and killed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And Abimelech fought against the city all that day. He captured the
        city and killed the people who were in it, and he razed the city and sowed
        it with salt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'When all the leaders of the Tower of Shechem heard of it, they entered
        the stronghold of the house of El-berith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Abimelech was told that all the leaders of the Tower of Shechem were
        gathered together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "And Abimelech went up to Mount Zalmon, he and all the people who
        were with him. And Abimelech took an axe in his hand and cut down a bundle
        of brushwood and took it up and laid it on his shoulder. And he said to the
        men who were with him, \u201CWhat you have seen me do, hurry and do as I
        have done.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'So every one of the people cut down his bundle and following Abimelech
        put it against the stronghold, and they set the stronghold on fire over them,
        so that all the people of the Tower of Shechem also died, about 1,000 men
        and women.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Then Abimelech went to Thebez and encamped against Thebez and captured
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'But there was a strong tower within the city, and all the men and
        women and all the leaders of the city fled to it and shut themselves in,
        and they went up to the roof of the tower. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'And Abimelech came to the tower and fought against it and drew near
        to the door of the tower to burn it with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "And a certain woman threw an upper millstone on Abimelech\u2019s
        head and crushed his skull. "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "Then he called quickly to the young man his armor-bearer and said
        to him, \u201CDraw your sword and kill me, lest they say of me, \u2018A woman
        killed him.\u2019\u201D And his young man thrust him through, and he died. "
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'And when the men of Israel saw that Abimelech was dead, everyone
        departed to his home. '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'Thus God returned the evil of Abimelech, which he committed against
        his father in killing his seventy brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: And God also made all the evil of the men of Shechem return on their
        heads, and upon them came the curse of Jotham the son of Jerubbaal.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Tola and Jair'
      title: Tola and Jair
      number: 1
      content: '  After Abimelech there arose to save Israel Tola the son of Puah,
        son of Dodo, a man of Issachar, and he lived at Shamir in the hill country
        of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he judged Israel twenty-three years. Then he died and was buried
        at Shamir.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'After him arose Jair the Gileadite, who judged Israel twenty-two
        years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he had thirty sons who rode on thirty donkeys, and they had thirty
        cities, called Havvoth-jair to this day, which are in the land of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Further Disobedience and Oppression'
      title: Further Disobedience and Oppression
      number: 5
      content: 'And Jair died and was buried in Kamon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  The people of Israel again did what was evil in the sight of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  and served the Baals and the Ashtaroth, the
        gods of Syria, the gods of Sidon, the gods of Moab, the gods of the Ammonites,
        and the gods of the Philistines. And they forsook the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and did not serve him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was kindled against
        Israel, and he sold them into the hand of the Philistines and into the hand
        of the Ammonites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and they crushed and oppressed the people of Israel that year. For
        eighteen years they oppressed all the people of Israel who were beyond the
        Jordan in the land of the Amorites, which is in Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the Ammonites crossed the Jordan to fight also against Judah
        and against Benjamin and against the house of Ephraim, so that Israel was
        severely distressed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the people of Israel cried out to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        saying, \u201CWe have sinned against you, because we have forsaken our God
        and have served the Baals.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to the people of Israel,
        \u201CDid I not save you from the Egyptians and from the Amorites, from the
        Ammonites and from the Philistines? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The Sidonians also, and the Amalekites and the Maonites oppressed
        you, and you cried out to me, and I saved you out of their hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Yet you have forsaken me and served other gods; therefore I will
        save you no more. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Go and cry out to the gods whom you have chosen; let them save you
        in the time of your distress.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And the people of Israel said to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u201CWe have sinned; do to us whatever seems good to you. Only please deliver
        us this day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So they put away the foreign gods from among them and served the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and he became impatient over the misery of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then the Ammonites were called to arms, and they encamped in Gilead.
        And the people of Israel came together, and they encamped at Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And the people, the leaders of Gilead, said one to another, \u201CWho
        is the man who will begin to fight against the Ammonites? He shall be head
        over all the inhabitants of Gilead.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jephthah Delivers Israel'
      title: Jephthah Delivers Israel
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Jephthah the Gileadite was a mighty warrior, but he was the
        son of a prostitute. Gilead was the father of Jephthah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Gilead\u2019s wife also bore him sons. And when his wife\u2019s
        sons grew up, they drove Jephthah out and said to him, \u201CYou shall not
        have an inheritance in our father\u2019s house, for you are the son of another
        woman.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Jephthah fled from his brothers and lived in the land of Tob,
        and worthless fellows collected around Jephthah and went out with him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'After a time the Ammonites made war against Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And when the Ammonites made war against Israel, the elders of Gilead
        went to bring Jephthah from the land of Tob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And they said to Jephthah, \u201CCome and be our leader, that we
        may fight against the Ammonites.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But Jephthah said to the elders of Gilead, \u201CDid you not hate
        me and drive me out of my father\u2019s house? Why have you come to me now
        when you are in distress?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the elders of Gilead said to Jephthah, \u201CThat is why we have
        turned to you now, that you may go with us and fight against the Ammonites
        and be our head over all the inhabitants of Gilead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Jephthah said to the elders of Gilead, \u201CIf you bring me home
        again to fight against the Ammonites, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gives them over to me, I will be your head.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the elders of Gilead said to Jephthah, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will be witness between us, if we do not do as you say.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Jephthah went with the elders of Gilead, and the people made him
        head and leader over them. And Jephthah spoke all his words before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        at Mizpah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Jephthah sent messengers to the king of the Ammonites and said,
        \u201CWhat do you have against me, that you have come to me to fight against
        my land?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the king of the Ammonites answered the messengers of Jephthah,
        \u201CBecause Israel on coming up from Egypt took away my land, from the
        Arnon to the Jabbok and to the Jordan; now therefore restore it peaceably.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Jephthah again sent messengers to the king of the Ammonites '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and said to him, \u201CThus says Jephthah: Israel did not take away
        the land of Moab or the land of the Ammonites, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'but when they came up from Egypt, Israel went through the wilderness
        to the Red Sea and came to Kadesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Israel then sent messengers to the king of Edom, saying, \u2018Please
        let us pass through your land,\u2019 but the king of Edom would not listen.
        And they sent also to the king of Moab, but he would not consent. So Israel
        remained at Kadesh.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThen they journeyed through the wilderness and went around
        the land of Edom and the land of Moab and arrived on the east side of the
        land of Moab and camped on the other side of the Arnon. But they did not
        enter the territory of Moab, for the Arnon was the boundary of Moab. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Israel then sent messengers to Sihon king of the Amorites, king of
        Heshbon, and Israel said to him, \u2018Please let us pass through your land
        to our country,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'but Sihon did not trust Israel to pass through his territory, so
        Sihon gathered all his people together and encamped at Jahaz and fought with
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel, gave Sihon
        and all his people into the hand of Israel, and they defeated them. So Israel
        took possession of all the land of the Amorites, who inhabited that country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And they took possession of all the territory of the Amorites from
        the Arnon to the Jabbok and from the wilderness to the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel, dispossessed
        the Amorites from before his people Israel; and are you to take possession
        of them? '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Will you not possess what Chemosh your god gives you to possess?
        And all that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God has dispossessed before
        us, we will possess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now are you any better than Balak the son of Zippor, king of Moab?
        Did he ever contend against Israel, or did he ever go to war with them? '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'While Israel lived in Heshbon and its villages, and in Aroer and
        its villages, and in all the cities that are on the banks of the Arnon, 300
        years, why did you not deliver them within that time? '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "I therefore have not sinned against you, and you do me wrong by making
        war on me. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the Judge, decide this day between
        the people of Israel and the people of Ammon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "28: Jephthah\u2019s Tragic Vow"
      title: "Jephthah\u2019s Tragic Vow"
      number: 28
      content: 'But the king of the Ammonites did not listen to the words of Jephthah
        that he sent to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '  Then the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was upon Jephthah,
        and he passed through Gilead and Manasseh and passed on to Mizpah of Gilead,
        and from Mizpah of Gilead he passed on to the Ammonites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And Jephthah made a vow to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and said,
        \u201CIf you will give the Ammonites into my hand, "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "then whatever[[COMMENT(0)]] comes out from the doors of my house
        to meet me when I return in peace from the Ammonites shall be the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s,
        and I will offer it up for a burnt offering.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '11:31 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So Jephthah crossed over to the Ammonites to fight against them,
        and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave them into his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And he struck them from Aroer to the neighborhood of Minnith, twenty
        cities, and as far as Abel-keramim, with a great blow. So the Ammonites were
        subdued before the people of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then Jephthah came to his home at Mizpah. And behold, his daughter
        came out to meet him with tambourines and with dances. She was his only child;
        besides her he had neither son nor daughter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And as soon as he saw her, he tore his clothes and said, \u201CAlas,
        my daughter! You have brought me very low, and you have become the cause
        of great trouble to me. For I have opened my mouth to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and I cannot take back my vow.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And she said to him, \u201CMy father, you have opened your mouth
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; do to me according to what has gone out
        of your mouth, now that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has avenged you on
        your enemies, on the Ammonites.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "So she said to her father, \u201CLet this thing be done for me: leave
        me alone two months, that I may go up and down on the mountains and weep
        for my virginity, I and my companions.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "So he said, \u201CGo.\u201D Then he sent her away for two months,
        and she departed, she and her companions, and wept for her virginity on the
        mountains. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And at the end of two months, she returned to her father, who did
        with her according to his vow that he had made. She had never known a man,
        and it became a custom in Israel '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: that the daughters of Israel went year by year to lament the daughter
        of Jephthah the Gileadite four days in the year.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jephthah\u2019s Conflict with Ephraim"
      title: "Jephthah\u2019s Conflict with Ephraim"
      number: 1
      content: "    The men of Ephraim were called to arms, and they crossed to Zaphon
        and said to Jephthah, \u201CWhy did you cross over to fight against the Ammonites
        and did not call us to go with you? We will burn your house over you with
        fire.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Jephthah said to them, \u201CI and my people had a great dispute
        with the Ammonites, and when I called you, you did not save me from their
        hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And when I saw that you would not save me, I took my life in my hand
        and crossed over against the Ammonites, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gave them into my hand. Why then have you come up to me this day to fight
        against me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Jephthah gathered all the men of Gilead and fought with Ephraim.
        And the men of Gilead struck Ephraim, because they said, \u201CYou are fugitives
        of Ephraim, you Gileadites, in the midst of Ephraim and Manasseh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the Gileadites captured the fords of the Jordan against the Ephraimites.
        And when any of the fugitives of Ephraim said, \u201CLet me go over,\u201D
        the men of Gilead said to him, \u201CAre you an Ephraimite?\u201D When he
        said, \u201CNo,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "they said to him, \u201CThen say Shibboleth,\u201D and he said, \u201CSibboleth,\u201D
        for he could not pronounce it right. Then they seized him and slaughtered
        him at the fords of the Jordan. At that time 42,000 of the Ephraimites fell.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Ibzan, Elon, and Abdon'
      title: Ibzan, Elon, and Abdon
      number: 7
      content: 'Jephthah judged Israel six years. Then Jephthah the Gileadite died
        and was buried in his city in Gilead.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:7 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'After him Ibzan of Bethlehem judged Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He had thirty sons, and thirty daughters he gave in marriage outside
        his clan, and thirty daughters he brought in from outside for his sons. And
        he judged Israel seven years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Ibzan died and was buried at Bethlehem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'After him Elon the Zebulunite judged Israel, and he judged Israel
        ten years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Elon the Zebulunite died and was buried at Aijalon in the land
        of Zebulun.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'After him Abdon the son of Hillel the Pirathonite judged Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He had forty sons and thirty grandsons, who rode on seventy donkeys,
        and he judged Israel eight years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Then Abdon the son of Hillel the Pirathonite died and was buried at
        Pirathon in the land of Ephraim, in the hill country of the Amalekites.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Birth of Samson'
      title: The Birth of Samson
      number: 1
      content: '  And the people of Israel again did what was evil in the sight of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, so the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave
        them into the hand of the Philistines for forty years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'There was a certain man of Zorah, of the tribe of the Danites, whose
        name was Manoah. And his wife was barren and had no children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> appeared to the
        woman and said to her, \u201CBehold, you are barren and have not borne children,
        but you shall conceive and bear a son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Therefore be careful and drink no wine or strong drink, and eat nothing
        unclean, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "for behold, you shall conceive and bear a son. No razor shall come
        upon his head, for the child shall be a Nazirite to God from the womb, and
        he shall begin to save Israel from the hand of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the woman came and told her husband, \u201CA man of God came
        to me, and his appearance was like the appearance of the angel of God, very
        awesome. I did not ask him where he was from, and he did not tell me his
        name, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "but he said to me, \u2018Behold, you shall conceive and bear a son.
        So then drink no wine or strong drink, and eat nothing unclean, for the child
        shall be a Nazirite to God from the womb to the day of his death.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Manoah prayed to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and said, \u201CO
        Lord, please let the man of God whom you sent come again to us and teach
        us what we are to do with the child who will be born.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And God listened to the voice of Manoah, and the angel of God came
        again to the woman as she sat in the field. But Manoah her husband was not
        with her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So the woman ran quickly and told her husband, \u201CBehold, the
        man who came to me the other day has appeared to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Manoah arose and went after his wife and came to the man and
        said to him, \u201CAre you the man who spoke to this woman?\u201D And he
        said, \u201CI am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Manoah said, \u201CNow when your words come true, what is to
        be the child\u2019s manner of life, and what is his mission?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Manoah,
        \u201COf all that I said to the woman let her be careful. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "She may not eat of anything that comes from the vine, neither let
        her drink wine or strong drink, or eat any unclean thing. All that I commanded
        her let her observe.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Manoah said to the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CPlease
        let us detain you and prepare a young goat for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Manoah,
        \u201CIf you detain me, I will not eat of your food. But if you prepare a
        burnt offering, then offer it to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D (For
        Manoah did not know that he was the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Manoah said to the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u201CWhat is your name, so that, when your words come true, we may honor
        you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to him, \u201CWhy
        do you ask my name, seeing it is wonderful?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Manoah took the young goat with the grain offering, and offered
        it on the rock to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, to the one who works[[COMMENT(0)]]
        wonders, and Manoah and his wife were watching. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:19 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And when the flame went up toward heaven from the altar, the angel
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> went up in the flame of the altar. Now
        Manoah and his wife were watching, and they fell on their faces to the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> appeared no more to
        Manoah and to his wife. Then Manoah knew that he was the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Manoah said to his wife, \u201CWe shall surely die, for we have
        seen God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But his wife said to him, \u201CIf the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had meant to kill us, he would not have accepted a burnt offering and a grain
        offering at our hands, or shown us all these things, or now announced to
        us such things as these.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And the woman bore a son and called his name Samson. And the young
        man grew, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> blessed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> began to stir him
        in Mahaneh-dan, between Zorah and Eshtaol.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Samson\u2019s Marriage"
      title: "Samson\u2019s Marriage"
      number: 1
      content: '    Samson went down to Timnah, and at Timnah he saw one of the daughters
        of the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then he came up and told his father and mother, \u201CI saw one of
        the daughters of the Philistines at Timnah. Now get her for me as my wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But his father and mother said to him, \u201CIs there not a woman
        among the daughters of your relatives, or among all our people, that you
        must go to take a wife from the uncircumcised Philistines?\u201D But Samson
        said to his father, \u201CGet her for me, for she is right in my eyes.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'His father and mother did not know that it was from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        for he was seeking an opportunity against the Philistines. At that time the
        Philistines ruled over Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Samson went down with his father and mother to Timnah, and they
        came to the vineyards of Timnah. And behold, a young lion came toward him
        roaring. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rushed upon him,
        and although he had nothing in his hand, he tore the lion in pieces as one
        tears a young goat. But he did not tell his father or his mother what he
        had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then he went down and talked with the woman, and she was right in
        Samson\u2019s eyes.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'After some days he returned to take her. And he turned aside to see
        the carcass of the lion, and behold, there was a swarm of bees in the body
        of the lion, and honey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He scraped it out into his hands and went on, eating as he went.
        And he came to his father and mother and gave some to them, and they ate.
        But he did not tell them that he had scraped the honey from the carcass of
        the lion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'His father went down to the woman, and Samson prepared a feast there,
        for so the young men used to do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'As soon as the people saw him, they brought thirty companions to
        be with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Samson said to them, \u201CLet me now put a riddle to you. If
        you can tell me what it is, within the seven days of the feast, and find
        it out, then I will give you thirty linen garments and thirty changes of
        clothes, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "but if you cannot tell me what it is, then you shall give me thirty
        linen garments and thirty changes of clothes.\u201D And they said to him,
        \u201CPut your riddle, that we may hear it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And he said to them,\u201COut of the eater came something to eat.Out
        of the strong came something sweet.\u201DAnd in three days they could not
        solve the riddle.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "On the fourth[[COMMENT(0)]] day they said to Samson\u2019s wife,
        \u201CEntice your husband to tell us what the riddle is, lest we burn you
        and your father\u2019s house with fire. Have you invited us here to impoverish
        us?\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '14:15 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac; Hebrew '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Samson\u2019s wife wept over him and said, \u201CYou only hate
        me; you do not love me. You have put a riddle to my people, and you have
        not told me what it is.\u201D And he said to her, \u201CBehold, I have not
        told my father nor my mother, and shall I tell you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'She wept before him the seven days that their feast lasted, and on
        the seventh day he told her, because she pressed him hard. Then she told
        the riddle to her people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And the men of the city said to him on the seventh day before the
        sun went down,\u201CWhat is sweeter than honey?What is stronger than a lion?\u201DAnd
        he said to them,\u201CIf you had not plowed with my heifer,you would not
        have found out my riddle.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  And the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rushed upon him,
        and he went down to Ashkelon and struck down thirty men of the town and took
        their spoil and gave the garments to those who had told the riddle. In hot
        anger he went back to his father\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Samson\u2019s wife was given to his companion, who had been his
        best man."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Samson Defeats the Philistines'
      title: Samson Defeats the Philistines
      number: 1
      content: "  After some days, at the time of wheat harvest, Samson went to visit
        his wife with a young goat. And he said, \u201CI will go in to my wife in
        the chamber.\u201D But her father would not allow him to go in. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And her father said, \u201CI really thought that you utterly hated
        her, so I gave her to your companion. Is not her younger sister more beautiful
        than she? Please take her instead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Samson said to them, \u201CThis time I shall be innocent in regard
        to the Philistines, when I do them harm.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Samson went and caught 300 foxes and took torches. And he turned
        them tail to tail and put a torch between each pair of tails. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And when he had set fire to the torches, he let the foxes go into
        the standing grain of the Philistines and set fire to the stacked grain and
        the standing grain, as well as the olive orchards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the Philistines said, \u201CWho has done this?\u201D And they
        said, \u201CSamson, the son-in-law of the Timnite, because he has taken his
        wife and given her to his companion.\u201D And the Philistines came up and
        burned her and her father with fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Samson said to them, \u201CIf this is what you do, I swear I
        will be avenged on you, and after that I will quit.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he struck them hip and thigh with a great blow, and he went down
        and stayed in the cleft of the rock of Etam.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then the Philistines came up and encamped in Judah and made a raid
        on Lehi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the men of Judah said, \u201CWhy have you come up against us?\u201D
        They said, \u201CWe have come up to bind Samson, to do to him as he did to
        us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then 3,000 men of Judah went down to the cleft of the rock of Etam,
        and said to Samson, \u201CDo you not know that the Philistines are rulers
        over us? What then is this that you have done to us?\u201D And he said to
        them, \u201CAs they did to me, so have I done to them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CWe have come down to bind you, that we
        may give you into the hands of the Philistines.\u201D And Samson said to
        them, \u201CSwear to me that you will not attack me yourselves.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "They said to him, \u201CNo; we will only bind you and give you into
        their hands. We will surely not kill you.\u201D So they bound him with two
        new ropes and brought him up from the rock.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When he came to Lehi, the Philistines came shouting to meet him.
        Then the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rushed upon him, and the
        ropes that were on his arms became as flax that has caught fire, and his
        bonds melted off his hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And he found a fresh jawbone of a donkey, and put out his hand and
        took it, and with it he struck 1,000 men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Samson said,\u201CWith the jawbone of a donkey,heaps upon heaps,with
        the jawbone of a donkeyhave I struck down a thousand men.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'As soon as he had finished speaking, he threw away the jawbone out
        of his hand. And that place was called Ramath-lehi.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:17 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And he was very thirsty, and he called upon the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and said, \u201CYou have granted this great salvation by the hand of your
        servant, and shall I now die of thirst and fall into the hands of the uncircumcised?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And God split open the hollow place that is at Lehi, and water came
        out from it. And when he drank, his spirit returned, and he revived. Therefore
        the name of it was called En-hakkore;[[COMMENT(0)]] it is at Lehi to this
        day. '
      comments:
      - number: '15:19 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And he judged Israel in the days of the Philistines twenty years.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Samson and Delilah'
      title: Samson and Delilah
      number: 1
      content: '  Samson went to Gaza, and there he saw a prostitute, and he went
        in to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The Gazites were told, \u201CSamson has come here.\u201D And they
        surrounded the place and set an ambush for him all night at the gate of the
        city. They kept quiet all night, saying, \u201CLet us wait till the light
        of the morning; then we will kill him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But Samson lay till midnight, and at midnight he arose and took hold
        of the doors of the gate of the city and the two posts, and pulled them up,
        bar and all, and put them on his shoulders and carried them to the top of
        the hill that is in front of Hebron.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'After this he loved a woman in the Valley of Sorek, whose name was
        Delilah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the lords of the Philistines came up to her and said to her,
        \u201CSeduce him, and see where his great strength lies, and by what means
        we may overpower him, that we may bind him to humble him. And we will each
        give you 1,100 pieces of silver.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Delilah said to Samson, \u201CPlease tell me where your great
        strength lies, and how you might be bound, that one could subdue you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Samson said to her, \u201CIf they bind me with seven fresh bowstrings
        that have not been dried, then I shall become weak and be like any other
        man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the lords of the Philistines brought up to her seven fresh bowstrings
        that had not been dried, and she bound him with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now she had men lying in ambush in an inner chamber. And she said
        to him, \u201CThe Philistines are upon you, Samson!\u201D But he snapped
        the bowstrings, as a thread of flax snaps when it touches the fire. So the
        secret of his strength was not known.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Delilah said to Samson, \u201CBehold, you have mocked me and
        told me lies. Please tell me how you might be bound.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And he said to her, \u201CIf they bind me with new ropes that have
        not been used, then I shall become weak and be like any other man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So Delilah took new ropes and bound him with them and said to him,
        \u201CThe Philistines are upon you, Samson!\u201D And the men lying in ambush
        were in an inner chamber. But he snapped the ropes off his arms like a thread.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Delilah said to Samson, \u201CUntil now you have mocked me and
        told me lies. Tell me how you might be bound.\u201D And he said to her, \u201CIf
        you weave the seven locks of my head with the web and fasten it tight with
        the pin, then I shall become weak and be like any other man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So while he slept, Delilah took the seven locks of his head and wove
        them into the web.[[COMMENT(0)]] And she made them tight with the pin and
        said to him, \u201CThe Philistines are upon you, Samson!\u201D But he awoke
        from his sleep and pulled away the pin, the loom, and the web.  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:14 '
        content: 'Compare Septuagint; Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And she said to him, \u201CHow can you say, \u2018I love you,\u2019
        when your heart is not with me? You have mocked me these three times, and
        you have not told me where your great strength lies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And when she pressed him hard with her words day after day, and urged
        him, his soul was vexed to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he told her all his heart, and said to her, \u201CA razor has
        never come upon my head, for I have been a Nazirite to God from my mother\u2019s
        womb. If my head is shaved, then my strength will leave me, and I shall become
        weak and be like any other man.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When Delilah saw that he had told her all his heart, she sent and
        called the lords of the Philistines, saying, \u201CCome up again, for he
        has told me all his heart.\u201D Then the lords of the Philistines came up
        to her and brought the money in their hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'She made him sleep on her knees. And she called a man and had him
        shave off the seven locks of his head. Then she began to torment him, and
        his strength left him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And she said, \u201CThe Philistines are upon you, Samson!\u201D And
        he awoke from his sleep and said, \u201CI will go out as at other times and
        shake myself free.\u201D But he did not know that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had left him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the Philistines seized him and gouged out his eyes and brought
        him down to Gaza and bound him with bronze shackles. And he ground at the
        mill in the prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: The Death of Samson'
      title: The Death of Samson
      number: 22
      content: 'But the hair of his head began to grow again after it had been shaved.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Now the lords of the Philistines gathered to offer a great sacrifice
        to Dagon their god and to rejoice, and they said, \u201COur god has given
        Samson our enemy into our hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And when the people saw him, they praised their god. For they said,
        \u201COur god has given our enemy into our hand, the ravager of our country,
        who has killed many of us.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:24 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And when their hearts were merry, they said, \u201CCall Samson, that
        he may entertain us.\u201D So they called Samson out of the prison, and he
        entertained them. They made him stand between the pillars. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And Samson said to the young man who held him by the hand, \u201CLet
        me feel the pillars on which the house rests, that I may lean against them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now the house was full of men and women. All the lords of the Philistines
        were there, and on the roof there were about 3,000 men and women, who looked
        on while Samson entertained.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Samson called to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and said, \u201CO
        Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>, please remember me and please strengthen
        me only this once, O God, that I may be avenged on the Philistines for my
        two eyes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And Samson grasped the two middle pillars on which the house rested,
        and he leaned his weight against them, his right hand on the one and his
        left hand on the other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And Samson said, \u201CLet me die with the Philistines.\u201D Then
        he bowed with all his strength, and the house fell upon the lords and upon
        all the people who were in it. So the dead whom he killed at his death were
        more than those whom he had killed during his life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Then his brothers and all his family came down and took him and brought
        him up and buried him between Zorah and Eshtaol in the tomb of Manoah his
        father. He had judged Israel twenty years.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Micah and the Levite'
      title: Micah and the Levite
      number: 1
      content: '  There was a man of the hill country of Ephraim, whose name was
        Micah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said to his mother, \u201CThe 1,100 pieces of silver that
        were taken from you, about which you uttered a curse, and also spoke it in
        my ears, behold, the silver is with me; I took it.\u201D And his mother said,
        \u201CBlessed be my son by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And he restored the 1,100 pieces of silver to his mother. And his
        mother said, \u201CI dedicate the silver to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        from my hand for my son, to make a carved image and a metal image. Now therefore
        I will restore it to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So when he restored the money to his mother, his mother took 200
        pieces of silver and gave it to the silversmith, who made it into a carved
        image and a metal image. And it was in the house of Micah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the man Micah had a shrine, and he made an ephod and household
        gods, and ordained[[COMMENT(0)]] one of his sons, who became his priest. '
      comments:
      - number: '17:5 '
        content: Hebrew ; also verse 12
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In those days there was no king in Israel. Everyone did what was
        right in his own eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now there was a young man of Bethlehem in Judah, of the family of
        Judah, who was a Levite, and he sojourned there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the man departed from the town of Bethlehem in Judah to sojourn
        where he could find a place. And as he journeyed, he came to the hill country
        of Ephraim to the house of Micah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Micah said to him, \u201CWhere do you come from?\u201D And he
        said to him, \u201CI am a Levite of Bethlehem in Judah, and I am going to
        sojourn where I may find a place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Micah said to him, \u201CStay with me, and be to me a father
        and a priest, and I will give you ten pieces of silver a year and a suit
        of clothes and your living.\u201D And the Levite went in. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the Levite was content to dwell with the man, and the young man
        became to him like one of his sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Micah ordained the Levite, and the young man became his priest,
        and was in the house of Micah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Micah said, \u201CNow I know that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will prosper me, because I have a Levite as priest.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Danites Take the Levite and the Idol'
      title: Danites Take the Levite and the Idol
      number: 1
      content: '    In those days there was no king in Israel. And in those days
        the tribe of the people of Dan was seeking for itself an inheritance to dwell
        in, for until then no inheritance among the tribes of Israel had fallen to
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So the people of Dan sent five able men from the whole number of
        their tribe, from Zorah and from Eshtaol, to spy out the land and to explore
        it. And they said to them, \u201CGo and explore the land.\u201D And they
        came to the hill country of Ephraim, to the house of Micah, and lodged there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "When they were by the house of Micah, they recognized the voice of
        the young Levite. And they turned aside and said to him, \u201CWho brought
        you here? What are you doing in this place? What is your business here?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CThis is how Micah dealt with me: he has
        hired me, and I have become his priest.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CInquire of God, please, that we may know
        whether the journey on which we are setting out will succeed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the priest said to them, \u201CGo in peace. The journey on which
        you go is under the eye of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the five men departed and came to Laish and saw the people who
        were there, how they lived in security, after the manner of the Sidonians,
        quiet and unsuspecting, lacking[[COMMENT(0)]] nothing that is in the earth
        and possessing wealth, and how they were far from the Sidonians and had no
        dealings with anyone. '
      comments:
      - number: '18:7 '
        content: Compare 18:10; the meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And when they came to their brothers at Zorah and Eshtaol, their
        brothers said to them, \u201CWhat do you report?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "They said, \u201CArise, and let us go up against them, for we have
        seen the land, and behold, it is very good. And will you do nothing? Do not
        be slow to go, to enter in and possess the land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "As soon as you go, you will come to an unsuspecting people. The land
        is spacious, for God has given it into your hands, a place where there is
        no lack of anything that is in the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So 600 men of the tribe of Dan, armed with weapons of war, set out
        from Zorah and Eshtaol, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and went up and encamped at Kiriath-jearim in Judah. On this account
        that place is called Mahaneh-dan[[COMMENT(0)]] to this day; behold, it is
        west of Kiriath-jearim. '
      comments:
      - number: '18:12 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And they passed on from there to the hill country of Ephraim, and
        came to the house of Micah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the five men who had gone to scout out the country of Laish
        said to their brothers, \u201CDo you know that in these houses there are
        an ephod, household gods, a carved image, and a metal image? Now therefore
        consider what you will do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And they turned aside there and came to the house of the young Levite,
        at the home of Micah, and asked him about his welfare. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now the 600 men of the Danites, armed with their weapons of war,
        stood by the entrance of the gate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the five men who had gone to scout out the land went up and entered
        and took the carved image, the ephod, the household gods, and the metal image,
        while the priest stood by the entrance of the gate with the 600 men armed
        with weapons of war. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And when these went into Micah\u2019s house and took the carved image,
        the ephod, the household gods, and the metal image, the priest said to them,
        \u201CWhat are you doing?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CKeep quiet; put your hand on your mouth
        and come with us and be to us a father and a priest. Is it better for you
        to be priest to the house of one man, or to be priest to a tribe and clan
        in Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And the priest\u2019s heart was glad. He took the ephod and the household
        gods and the carved image and went along with the people.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So they turned and departed, putting the little ones and the livestock
        and the goods in front of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "When they had gone a distance from the home of Micah, the men who
        were in the houses near Micah\u2019s house were called out, and they overtook
        the people of Dan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And they shouted to the people of Dan, who turned around and said
        to Micah, \u201CWhat is the matter with you, that you come with such a company?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And he said, \u201CYou take my gods that I made and the priest, and
        go away, and what have I left? How then do you ask me, \u2018What is the
        matter with you?\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And the people of Dan said to him, \u201CDo not let your voice be
        heard among us, lest angry fellows fall upon you, and you lose your life
        with the lives of your household.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then the people of Dan went their way. And when Micah saw that they
        were too strong for him, he turned and went back to his home.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But the people of Dan took what Micah had made, and the priest who
        belonged to him, and they came to Laish, to a people quiet and unsuspecting,
        and struck them with the edge of the sword and burned the city with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And there was no deliverer because it was far from Sidon, and they
        had no dealings with anyone. It was in the valley that belongs to Beth-rehob.
        Then they rebuilt the city and lived in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And they named the city Dan, after the name of Dan their ancestor,
        who was born to Israel; but the name of the city was Laish at the first. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And the people of Dan set up the carved image for themselves, and
        Jonathan the son of Gershom, son of Moses,[[COMMENT(0)]]  and his sons were
        priests to the tribe of the Danites until the day of the captivity of the
        land. '
      comments:
      - number: '18:30 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "So they set up Micah\u2019s carved image that he made, as long as
        the house of God was at Shiloh."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Levite and His Concubine'
      title: A Levite and His Concubine
      number: 1
      content: '  In those days, when there was no king in Israel, a certain Levite
        was sojourning in the remote parts of the hill country of Ephraim, who took
        to himself a concubine from Bethlehem in Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And his concubine was unfaithful to[[COMMENT(0)]] him, and she went
        away from him to her father\u2019s house at Bethlehem in Judah, and was there
        some four months. "
      comments:
      - number: '19:2 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Old Latin '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then her husband arose and went after her, to speak kindly to her
        and bring her back. He had with him his servant and a couple of donkeys.
        And she brought him into her father\u2019s house. And when the girl\u2019s
        father saw him, he came with joy to meet him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And his father-in-law, the girl\u2019s father, made him stay, and
        he remained with him three days. So they ate and drank and spent the night
        there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And on the fourth day they arose early in the morning, and he prepared
        to go, but the girl\u2019s father said to his son-in-law, \u201CStrengthen
        your heart with a morsel of bread, and after that you may go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So the two of them sat and ate and drank together. And the girl\u2019s
        father said to the man, \u201CBe pleased to spend the night, and let your
        heart be merry.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when the man rose up to go, his father-in-law pressed him, till
        he spent the night there again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And on the fifth day he arose early in the morning to depart. And
        the girl\u2019s father said, \u201CStrengthen your heart and wait until the
        day declines.\u201D So they ate, both of them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And when the man and his concubine and his servant rose up to depart,
        his father-in-law, the girl\u2019s father, said to him, \u201CBehold, now
        the day has waned toward evening. Please, spend the night. Behold, the day
        draws to its close. Lodge here and let your heart be merry, and tomorrow
        you shall arise early in the morning for your journey, and go home.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But the man would not spend the night. He rose up and departed and
        arrived opposite Jebus (that is, Jerusalem). He had with him a couple of
        saddled donkeys, and his concubine was with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "When they were near Jebus, the day was nearly over, and the servant
        said to his master, \u201CCome now, let us turn aside to this city of the
        Jebusites and spend the night in it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And his master said to him, \u201CWe will not turn aside into the
        city of foreigners, who do not belong to the people of Israel, but we will
        pass on to Gibeah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And he said to his young man, \u201CCome and let us draw near to
        one of these places and spend the night at Gibeah or at Ramah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So they passed on and went their way. And the sun went down on them
        near Gibeah, which belongs to Benjamin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and they turned aside there, to go in and spend the night at Gibeah.
        And he went in and sat down in the open square of the city, for no one took
        them into his house to spend the night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And behold, an old man was coming from his work in the field at evening.
        The man was from the hill country of Ephraim, and he was sojourning in Gibeah.
        The men of the place were Benjaminites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he lifted up his eyes and saw the traveler in the open square
        of the city. And the old man said, \u201CWhere are you going? And where do
        you come from?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CWe are passing from Bethlehem in Judah
        to the remote parts of the hill country of Ephraim, from which I come. I
        went to Bethlehem in Judah, and I am going to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        but no one has taken me into his house. "
      comments:
      - number: '19:18 '
        content: Septuagint ; compare verse 29
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "We have straw and feed for our donkeys, with bread and wine for me
        and your female servant and the young man with your servants. There is no
        lack of anything.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And the old man said, \u201CPeace be to you; I will care for all
        your wants. Only, do not spend the night in the square.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "21: Gibeah\u2019s Crime"
      title: "Gibeah\u2019s Crime"
      number: 21
      content: 'So he brought him into his house and gave the donkeys feed. And they
        washed their feet, and ate and drank.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "As they were making their hearts merry, behold, the men of the city,
        worthless fellows, surrounded the house, beating on the door. And they said
        to the old man, the master of the house, \u201CBring out the man who came
        into your house, that we may know him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And the man, the master of the house, went out to them and said to
        them, \u201CNo, my brothers, do not act so wickedly; since this man has come
        into my house, do not do this vile thing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Behold, here are my virgin daughter and his concubine. Let me bring
        them out now. Violate them and do with them what seems good to you, but against
        this man do not do this outrageous thing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But the men would not listen to him. So the man seized his concubine
        and made her go out to them. And they knew her and abused her all night until
        the morning. And as the dawn began to break, they let her go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And as morning appeared, the woman came and fell down at the door
        of the man\u2019s house where her master was, until it was light.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And her master rose up in the morning, and when he opened the doors
        of the house and went out to go on his way, behold, there was his concubine
        lying at the door of the house, with her hands on the threshold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "He said to her, \u201CGet up, let us be going.\u201D But there was
        no answer. Then he put her on the donkey, and the man rose up and went away
        to his home. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And when he entered his house, he took a knife, and taking hold of
        his concubine he divided her, limb by limb, into twelve pieces, and sent
        her throughout all the territory of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And all who saw it said, \u201CSuch a thing has never happened or
        been seen from the day that the people of Israel came up out of the land
        of Egypt until this day; consider it, take counsel, and speak.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s War with the Tribe of Benjamin"
      title: "Israel\u2019s War with the Tribe of Benjamin"
      number: 1
      content: '  Then all the people of Israel came out, from Dan to Beersheba,
        including the land of Gilead, and the congregation assembled as one man to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> at Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the chiefs of all the people, of all the tribes of Israel, presented
        themselves in the assembly of the people of God, 400,000 men on foot that
        drew the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "(Now the people of Benjamin heard that the people of Israel had gone
        up to Mizpah.) And the people of Israel said, \u201CTell us, how did this
        evil happen?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the Levite, the husband of the woman who was murdered, answered
        and said, \u201CI came to Gibeah that belongs to Benjamin, I and my concubine,
        to spend the night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the leaders of Gibeah rose against me and surrounded the house
        against me by night. They meant to kill me, and they violated my concubine,
        and she is dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So I took hold of my concubine and cut her in pieces and sent her
        throughout all the country of the inheritance of Israel, for they have committed
        abomination and outrage in Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Behold, you people of Israel, all of you, give your advice and counsel
        here.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And all the people arose as one man, saying, \u201CNone of us will
        go to his tent, and none of us will return to his house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But now this is what we will do to Gibeah: we will go up against
        it by lot, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and we will take ten men of a hundred throughout all the tribes of
        Israel, and a hundred of a thousand, and a thousand of ten thousand, to bring
        provisions for the people, that when they come they may repay Gibeah of Benjamin
        for all the outrage that they have committed in Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So all the men of Israel gathered against the city, united as one
        man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  And the tribes of Israel sent men through all the tribe of Benjamin,
        saying, \u201CWhat evil is this that has taken place among you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now therefore give up the men, the worthless fellows in Gibeah, that
        we may put them to death and purge evil from Israel.\u201D But the Benjaminites
        would not listen to the voice of their brothers, the people of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the people of Benjamin came together out of the cities to Gibeah
        to go out to battle against the people of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the people of Benjamin mustered out of their cities on that day
        26,000 men who drew the sword, besides the inhabitants of Gibeah, who mustered
        700 chosen men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Among all these were 700 chosen men who were left-handed; every one
        could sling a stone at a hair and not miss. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the men of Israel, apart from Benjamin, mustered 400,000 men
        who drew the sword; all these were men of war.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The people of Israel arose and went up to Bethel and inquired of
        God, \u201CWho shall go up first for us to fight against the people of Benjamin?\u201D
        And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CJudah shall go up first.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then the people of Israel rose in the morning and encamped against
        Gibeah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the men of Israel went out to fight against Benjamin, and the
        men of Israel drew up the battle line against them at Gibeah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The people of Benjamin came out of Gibeah and destroyed on that day
        22,000 men of the Israelites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But the people, the men of Israel, took courage, and again formed
        the battle line in the same place where they had formed it on the first day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And the people of Israel went up and wept before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        until the evening. And they inquired of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u201CShall we again draw near to fight against our brothers, the people
        of Benjamin?\u201D And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CGo up
        against them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So the people of Israel came near against the people of Benjamin
        the second day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Benjamin went against them out of Gibeah the second day, and
        destroyed 18,000 men of the people of Israel. All these were men who drew
        the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then all the people of Israel, the whole army, went up and came to
        Bethel and wept. They sat there before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and
        fasted that day until evening, and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings
        before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And the people of Israel inquired of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        (for the ark of the covenant of God was there in those days, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "and Phinehas the son of Eleazar, son of Aaron, ministered before
        it in those days), saying, \u201CShall we go out once more to battle against
        our brothers, the people of Benjamin, or shall we cease?\u201D And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said, \u201CGo up, for tomorrow I will give them into your hand.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '  So Israel set men in ambush around Gibeah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And the people of Israel went up against the people of Benjamin on
        the third day and set themselves in array against Gibeah, as at other times. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And the people of Benjamin went out against the people and were drawn
        away from the city. And as at other times they began to strike and kill some
        of the people in the highways, one of which goes up to Bethel and the other
        to Gibeah, and in the open country, about thirty men of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And the people of Benjamin said, \u201CThey are routed before us,
        as at the first.\u201D But the people of Israel said, \u201CLet us flee and
        draw them away from the city to the highways.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And all the men of Israel rose up out of their place and set themselves
        in array at Baal-tamar, and the men of Israel who were in ambush rushed out
        of their place from Maareh-geba.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:33 '
        content: 'Some Septuagint manuscripts '
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And there came against Gibeah 10,000 chosen men out of all Israel,
        and the battle was hard, but the Benjaminites did not know that disaster
        was close upon them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> defeated Benjamin before Israel,
        and the people of Israel destroyed 25,100 men of Benjamin that day. All these
        were men who drew the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'So the people of Benjamin saw that they were defeated.The men of
        Israel gave ground to Benjamin, because they trusted the men in ambush whom
        they had set against Gibeah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Then the men in ambush hurried and rushed against Gibeah; the men
        in ambush moved out and struck all the city with the edge of the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Now the appointed signal between the men of Israel and the men in
        the main ambush was that when they made a great cloud of smoke rise up out
        of the city '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "the men of Israel should turn in battle. Now Benjamin had begun to
        strike and kill about thirty men of Israel. They said, \u201CSurely they
        are defeated before us, as in the first battle.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'But when the signal began to rise out of the city in a column of
        smoke, the Benjaminites looked behind them, and behold, the whole of the
        city went up in smoke to heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Then the men of Israel turned, and the men of Benjamin were dismayed,
        for they saw that disaster was close upon them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Therefore they turned their backs before the men of Israel in the
        direction of the wilderness, but the battle overtook them. And those who
        came out of the cities were destroying them in their midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Surrounding the Benjaminites, they pursued them and trod them down
        from Nohah[[COMMENT(0)]] as far as opposite Gibeah on the east. '
      comments:
      - number: '20:43 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew [at their] '
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Eighteen thousand men of Benjamin fell, all of them men of valor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And they turned and fled toward the wilderness to the rock of Rimmon.
        Five thousand men of them were cut down in the highways. And they were pursued
        hard to Gidom, and 2,000 men of them were struck down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'So all who fell that day of Benjamin were 25,000 men who drew the
        sword, all of them men of valor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'But 600 men turned and fled toward the wilderness to the rock of
        Rimmon and remained at the rock of Rimmon four months. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: And the men of Israel turned back against the people of Benjamin and
        struck them with the edge of the sword, the city, men and beasts and all
        that they found. And all the towns that they found they set on fire.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Wives Provided for the Tribe of Benjamin'
      title: Wives Provided for the Tribe of Benjamin
      number: 1
      content: "  Now the men of Israel had sworn at Mizpah, \u201CNo one of us shall
        give his daughter in marriage to Benjamin.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the people came to Bethel and sat there till evening before God,
        and they lifted up their voices and wept bitterly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And they said, \u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,
        why has this happened in Israel, that today there should be one tribe lacking
        in Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the next day the people rose early and built there an altar and
        offered burnt offerings and peace offerings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the people of Israel said, \u201CWhich of all the tribes of Israel
        did not come up in the assembly to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?\u201D
        For they had taken a great oath concerning him who did not come up to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to Mizpah, saying, \u201CHe shall surely be put
        to death.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the people of Israel had compassion for Benjamin their brother
        and said, \u201COne tribe is cut off from Israel this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "What shall we do for wives for those who are left, since we have
        sworn by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that we will not give them any of
        our daughters for wives?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And they said, \u201CWhat one is there of the tribes of Israel that
        did not come up to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to Mizpah?\u201D And behold,
        no one had come to the camp from Jabesh-gilead, to the assembly. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For when the people were mustered, behold, not one of the inhabitants
        of Jabesh-gilead was there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So the congregation sent 12,000 of their bravest men there and commanded
        them, \u201CGo and strike the inhabitants of Jabesh-gilead with the edge
        of the sword; also the women and the little ones. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "This is what you shall do: every male and every woman that has lain
        with a male you shall devote to destruction.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they found among the inhabitants of Jabesh-gilead 400 young virgins
        who had not known a man by lying with him, and they brought them to the camp
        at Shiloh, which is in the land of Canaan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then the whole congregation sent word to the people of Benjamin who
        were at the rock of Rimmon and proclaimed peace to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Benjamin returned at that time. And they gave them the women
        whom they had saved alive of the women of Jabesh-gilead, but they were not
        enough for them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the people had compassion on Benjamin because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had made a breach in the tribes of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then the elders of the congregation said, \u201CWhat shall we do
        for wives for those who are left, since the women are destroyed out of Benjamin?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And they said, \u201CThere must be an inheritance for the survivors
        of Benjamin, that a tribe not be blotted out from Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Yet we cannot give them wives from our daughters.\u201D For the people
        of Israel had sworn, \u201CCursed be he who gives a wife to Benjamin.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So they said, \u201CBehold, there is the yearly feast of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        at Shiloh, which is north of Bethel, on the east of the highway that goes
        up from Bethel to Shechem, and south of Lebonah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And they commanded the people of Benjamin, saying, \u201CGo and lie
        in ambush in the vineyards "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and watch. If the daughters of Shiloh come out to dance in the dances,
        then come out of the vineyards and snatch each man his wife from the daughters
        of Shiloh, and go to the land of Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And when their fathers or their brothers come to complain to us,
        we will say to them, \u2018Grant them graciously to us, because we did not
        take for each man of them his wife in battle, neither did you give them to
        them, else you would now be guilty.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And the people of Benjamin did so and took their wives, according
        to their number, from the dancers whom they carried off. Then they went and
        returned to their inheritance and rebuilt the towns and lived in them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And the people of Israel departed from there at that time, every
        man to his tribe and family, and they went out from there every man to his
        inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  In those days there was no king in Israel. Everyone did what was
        right in his own eyes.'
      comments: []
